    "rich_text_rDwnTU": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_m4gCCg": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "What we are looking for",
            "heading_tag": "h1",
            "text_color": "",
            "gradient": ""
          }
        },
        "richtext_p6jEMT": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>We’re looking to work with creators who genuinely care about their child’s development and see stories as something to be enjoyed, not something that feels like homework.</p><p>You might:</p><ul><li>Be raising a child who learns differently</li><li>Be finding ways to make reading feel calmer or more accessible</li><li>Want books to feel like an escape to exciting new worlds, rather than a task</li><li>A parent who struggles to get their kids off screens</li></ul><p>Most importantly, we want creators who are happy to share real, lived moments, not polished perfection.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_Ccg6qi": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "The Content",
            "heading_tag": "h4",
            "text_color": "",
            "gradient": ""
          }
        },
        "richtext_tPqtH3": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>We’d love you to show how Voxblock fits naturally into your family life and how you use it to encourage reading at home.</p><p>Some prompts to guide your content:</p><ul><li>Do you use Voxblock as part of your bedtime routine?</li><li>Do you read along to the audiobooks or let your child listen independently?</li><li>Has audio helped remove pressure around reading in your household?</li><li>Does your child choose stories more confidently when they’re in control?</li><li>Does your child multitask while listening?</li><li>How has it helped you, as a parent?</li></ul><p>There’s no script to follow, we’re far more interested in your honest experience and what works for your family. Consider content from both your child’s point of view and from you as a parent (everybody loves a good parenting hack).</p><p>There is no restrictions on the form of content, a mixture of video and static imagery will be fine. But please make sure your content includes the product in action.</p><h5>Key message to weave in</h5><ul><li>All reading doesn’t look the same</li><li>Listening is reading</li><li>Reading can be calm, comforting and fun</li></ul><h5>Tone & style</h5><ul><li>Natural and relaxed</li><li>Warm, honest and relatable</li><li>Family-focused and realistic</li><li>No hard selling</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
